    A three coloring of a set of vertices
    ThreeColoringProblem
    Defines the Reduction steps for a 3-Coloring problem on directed graphs
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicThreeColoring<V>
    A three coloring of a set of vertices.
    Compute3Coloring
    Main Class instantiating and running the SAT solver
    Type1ThreeColoringProblem
    A coloring is valid iff (a) it only uses three colors (red, green, blue); (b) no two adjacent vertices are colored both blue; and (c) all vertices colored green or red have at least one successor colored blue.
    Type2ThreeColoringProblem
    A coloring is valid iff (a) it only uses three colors (red, green, blue); (b) no two adjacent vertices are colored both blue; (c) all neighbors of blue vertices are labeled red; (d) all vertices colored red have at least one successor colored blue; and (e) at least one vertex is colored blue.
